[{"id":"VR803941","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures, labeled Figure 1 and Figure 2, each show a horizontal wire carrying current I to the right through the center of a circle with its plane oriented perpendicular to the wire. The circle in figure 1 has area A, and the circle in figure 2 has area 2 A.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR803941.g03.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> shows a wire with current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span> to the right passing through the center of a circle having area <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>A</mi></math></span></span>. The plane of the circle is oriented perpendicular to the wire. The magnetic field at a location on the perimeter of the circle has magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>B</mi></math></span></span>. Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> shows the same wire passing through the center of a circle having area <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 A\"><math alttext=\"2 A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>A</mi></math></span></span>. Which of the following represents the magnetic field at a location on the perimeter of the circle in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR803941_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator B, and denominator 4\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator B, and denominator 4\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>B</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator B, and denominator 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator B, and denominator 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator B, and denominator the square root of 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator B, and denominator the square root of 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>B</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 B\"><math alttext=\"2 B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>B</mi></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]